    "breadcrumb": "Lego \u003e Obtain or renew certificates",
    "content": "This guide explains how to get and renew a certificate with the HTTP-01 challenge.\nNote The examples require that the lego binary has permission to bind to ports 80.\nIf your environment does not allow you to bind to these ports, please read Running without root privileges and Port Usage.\nUsing the built-in web server ​ Classic Way With a Configuration File Execute the following command:\nlego run -d 'example.com' --http To know the available options, read the documentation.\nCreate a .lego.yml file with the following content:\ncertificates: foo: challenge: http-01 domains: - example.com And execute:\nlego To know the available options, read the documentation.\nUsing an existing, running web server If you have an existing server running on port 80, the --http option also requires the --http.webroot option. This just writes the http-01 challenge token to the given directory in the folder .well-known/acme-challenge and does not start a server.\nThe given directory should be publicly served as / on the domain(s) for the validation to complete.\nIf the given directory is not publicly served, you will have to support rewriting the request to the directory;\nYou could also implement a rewrite to rewrite .well-known/acme-challenge to the given directory .well-known/acme-challenge.\nYou should be able to run an existing webserver on port 80 and have lego write the token file with the HTTP-01 challenge key authorization to \u003cwebroot dir\u003e/.well-known/acme-challenge/ by running something like:\n​ Classic Way With a Configuration File Execute the following command:\nlego run --http --http.webroot /path/to/webroot --domains example.com To know the available options, read the documentation.\nCreate a .lego.yml file with the following content:\nchallenges: mychallenge: http: webroot: /tmp/webroot certificates: foo: challenge: mychallenge domains: - example.com And execute:\nlego To know the available options, read the documentation.",
    "description": "This guide explains how to get and renew a certificate with the HTTP-01 challenge.",
    "tags": [],
    "title": "HTTP-01 Challenge",
    "uri": "/lego/obtain/http01/index.html"
